reviews_data.review_text: This place is so cute! Couches and seats for your whole group! Books on display, Christian music in the background, and wonderful drinks to enjoy. The bathroom is absolutely adorable and clean. Payed $8 for a small cup about the size of a medium at starbucks. Definitely recommend. Totally worth it. 9.75/10

So cute and cozy! The people are patient and calm even during rush hour. They play Christian music in the background low enough for you to concentrate. There are plenty of cozy couches and chairs to sit and enjoy your coffee and or pastry. I didn't even know this place existed untill i got curious and went inside. I HIGHLY recommend this place.

My mum and I came in, the atmosphere was immediately welcoming and the interior was set up very nicely. We walked up to order and the barista was really kind and was starting on another person's order but was still attentive to us. We only waited a little bit, I would say a 5-8 minute mark but we did have someone who ordered before us with three drinks, so that is a pretty good time. The coffees we ordered were amazing. Would recommend the James Bond and the Sweet Summer drink. They are only seasonal however. Very amazing coffee!
Best whole roasted coffee beans I've found in the Charlotte area.
Staff knows their regulars by name. I was new to the cafe and felt welcomed. Greeted with a smile.

Cabbella's is my go-to coffee shop! While visiting NC over the past few years I would pop in and fell in love with the atmosphere here. Now that I live here, it is the only coffee shop for me!

Elena is my regular barista and is so kind and caring towards all of her customers. You can tell she takes the time to get to know them, ready to serve their usuals, but also stretches us out of our routine in suggesting new drinks and food that have been crafted!

I hold a small Bible Study group here every other Saturday at 10 am and all of my participants love the coffee, food, and atmosphere as much as I do!

So happy to have Cabbella's to enjoy! Be sure to try the Booty Blend drip coffee, a Dirty Luck chai, Laugh blended coffee, or even a Strawberry-Banana smoothie!! Don't forget to try a quiche (all are excellent), breads, scones,muffins.....No matter what you choose I'm sure you will love it!! ☕️

I really want to like this coffee shop, it’s cute and comfortable to sit and relax with friends and family- but the coffee. I have gone a few times now and I don’t know if it’s the coffee, the flavors, or what but it consistently tastes like rubbing alcohol. Or like a bad liqueur.
Nice little coffee shop to stop in and stay a while. Friendly service and comfortable atmosphere.
loved everything about this place from friendly staff to food, definitely recommend
I have always loved this place. The coffee is great quality and taste. The dirty chai latte is so good!
Excellent coffee & service.
Confused by these ratings. This coffee is terrible. The staff was friendly so I’ll give them that.
If you want quality coffee and service this is the place to go in Denver! Best atmosphere than any shop around!
Some of the best cold brew I've ever had. Every time we go in, the barista recognizes us and knows our order. It's one of our favorite weekend stops!
Great coffee choices and baked goods. Gluten-free options are also available.

Stopped by recently for a visit at Cabbella's Coffee Shop and it was fantastic!  The lady working behind the counter was very helpful and service was great.  We had the Snickerdoodle Latee, Strawberry Banana Smoothie and a Plain Bagel with Cream Cheese.  Everything was great and we look forward to another visit!  Highly recommend!
Great coffee and service!  Bought some treats to take home, they were delicious!

We had a great experience at Cabella’s. Savannah was lovely! She gave great recommendations and provided top notch service. Our drinks were delicious. We’ll be sure to stop by here any time we’re vacationing around Lake Norman.
Cabellas coffee is a Denver staple. I look forward to coming here anytime I’m in town! Not only for the great coffee, but the amazing employees as well!

Great place to hang out, work, meet, or just to stop in. Baristas are willing to make you anything you want and there is something on the menu for everyone (even kids and non coffee drinkers). Love that all of their baked goods are sourced from local bakers too
Cabella’s is the best and the vibe is unmatched. I really love their smoothies and my son absolutely loves the coffee and muffins! Parking was great as well!
I love Cabella’s coffee and the atmosphere is so inviting. I highly recommend it!
Great family owned business and the coffee is the best around!
No better community Coffee meeting experience in All of Denver!!

I'm only in Denver twice a year (for Dentist Appointments). But every time I'm in town, I have to stop in Cabbella's and see my man J.R. for some delicious coffee! J.R., quite simply, is the man! All of his drinks are incredible; my personal favorite is the caramel frappe with whip cream. J.R. is very friendly and a lot of fun to talk to. The atmosphere is warm and inviting with plenty of places to hang out and a variety of couches, tables, chairs, etc., so if I have some time to stay a while and work remotely, I'll do it! Highly recommend! Coffee shops like Cabella's that focus on a quality product, incredible customer service, and a laid back vibe are rare!

I was in the area for a sales appointment and stopped in for a snack and coffee. I never made it to the coffee, because they had such an awesome smoothie selection. It was fantastic, and the atmosphere was super laid back. The biscotti was delicious as well. I wish I had a place like this in my town.

I have found a new coffee café. It's a little tricky getting in and out of the parking lot, but it's so worth it. The menu includes everything you would expect to find at a great coffee shop. It's family owned, so the atmosphere is very inviting and warm.
